This paper discusses optimization techniques for machine learning models, specifically natural gradient descent. The paper focuses on the limitations of the empirical Fisher approximation, which is commonly used in machine learning optimization algorithms. Given this focus, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
